     <body>
     <div type="epigraph">
   <pb facs="4"/>
   <head>In Authorem.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>
         <hi>THOV,</hi> that wouldst finde the habit of true passion,</l>
      <l>And see a minde attir'd in perfect straines;</l>
      <l>Not wearing moodes, as gallants doe a fashion,</l>
      <l>In these pide times, only to shewe their braines,</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Looke here on <hi>Bretons</hi> worke, the master print:</l>
      <l>Where, such perfections to the life doe rise.</l>
      <l>If they seeme wry, to such as looke asquint,</l>
      <l>The fault's not in the obiect, but their eyes.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>For, as one comming with a laterall viewe,</l>
      <l>Vnto a cunning piece wrought perspectiue,</l>
      <l>Wants facultie to make a censure true:</l>
      <l>So with this Authors Readers will it thriue:</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Which being eyed directly, I diuine,</l>
      <l>His proofe their praise, will meete, as in this line.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>BEN: IOHNSON.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
